Recent GitHub pull requests for the elizaOS/eliza repository include several bugfixes, features, and other improvements:

Bugfixes:
- Fixed agent response and improved logging/tracing in bootstrap plugin (#4548)
- Fixed bad environment resolution (#4547)
- Removed banner display and improved help command formatting (#4546)
- Added passthrough function to prevent LLM plugins from breaking (#4544)
- Fixed integration test import (#4541)
- Fixed error related to TEXT_EMBEDDING issue #4336 (#4537)
- Fixed build for Discord plugin and service after merge conflict (#4552)
- Updated TEE for CI (#4572)
- Updated Telegram messageManager tests to expect MarkdownV2 (#4570)

Features:
- Added commit SHA to CLI cache action (#4571)
- Added support for third-party plugin installation with tests (#4568)
- Upgraded CLI agent command (#4560)

Other improvements:
- Made environment naming consistent for project manager agent (#4549)
- Removed REST /ping for websocket status checks in client (#4551)
- Reverted to regular dev command (#4566)
- Updated to use latest v2 plugin list (#4564)
- Enabled strict types and adjusted guards for plugin-telegram (#4559)

Recent pull requests in the elizaOS/eliza repository include several feature additions and bug fixes. PR #4554 by 0xbbjoker adds MySQL support to the degen feature. User yungalgo has submitted multiple PRs (#4535, #4538, and #4543) related to ELIZA290/part-2 plugins agent CLI commands. PR #4573 by Samarthsinghal28 adds a Polygon Plugin, while PR #4574 by Y4NK33420 implements Polygon Gas Oracle Integration. Bug fixes include PR #4552 by 0xbbjoker addressing build issues for plugin discord and service mess after merge conflicts, and PR #4558 by ChristopherTrimboli fixing the Create room API. Additionally, PR #4575 by HarshModi2005 addresses Issue 451.

Four issues have been reported in the elizaOS/eliza repository. Issue #4536 reports a module resolution problem where the system cannot find the '@elizaos/core' module or its type declarations. Issue #4562 requests publishing the package to npm. Issue #4561 reports an error from CI activity. Issue #4565 indicates a missing path issue related to 'packages/docs/i18n/readme/'.

The elizaos/eliza repository showed continued development activity over a two-day period. From May 12-13, 2025, there were 20 new pull requests with 7 merged, 1 new issue, and 11 active contributors. The following day (May 13-14, 2025), activity remained strong with 16 new pull requests (10 merged), 3 new issues, and an increased contributor count of 17 active participants.

The sources provide information about the top contributors for the GitHub repository elizaOS/eliza. However, both sources appear to be identical and contain only the heading 'Top contributors for elizaOS/eliza' without listing any specific contributors or additional details.
